Arsenal’s squad to tackle West Ham United in today’s English Premier League fixture at the London Stadium has been revealed. Arsenal head to the game following a 2-1 defeat to Brighton in their last Premier League encounter. DAILY POST had reported that Arsenal interim manager, Freddie Ljungberg, has insisted he is the man to stop the rot at the club, ahead of West Ham clash.  Arsenal’s provisional squad against West Ham are Leno, Bellerin, Papastathopoulos, David Luiz, Kolasinac, Xhaka, Torreira, Aubameyang, Willock, Mesut Ozil, Lacazette, Kieran Tierney, Nicolas Pepe, Calum Chambers, Reiss Nelson, Emiliano Martinez, Matteo Guendouzi, Gabriel Martinelli The kick-off time for the match is 9pm. Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.